article.headline: Cornell 96, Harvard 75
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. -- Ryan Wittman scored 20 points and broke Cornell's record for career 3-pointers as the Big Red beat Harvard 96-75 and extended their home winning streak to 18. Wittman's 4-of-7 effort from beyond the arc brought him to 239 career points from the 3-point range, surpassing Cody Toppert's 237 points in 2005. Wittman, a junior, also added six assists and grabbed four rebounds. Chris Wroblewski had 17 points for Cornell (16-7, 6-1 Ivy), Adam Wire had 14, Louis Dale added 12 and Jeff Foote scored 10. Harvard (10-11, 2-5 Ivy) was led by 16 points and six assists by Drew Housman and 14 points from Max Kenyi. Jeremy Lin added 11.
